President Donald Trump has issued a proclamation declaring April 21-29, 2018 as National Park Week in the United States. The proclamation recognizes the importance of America's national parks in preserving the country's natural and cultural heritage. It highlights the power of nature and the scenic beauty found in the national parks, which attract millions of visitors each year. The proclamation also emphasizes the need to protect and revitalize the national parks through initiatives such as establishing a Public Lands Infrastructure Fund and encouraging public-private partnerships for upgrades and maintenance. The proclamation encourages Americans to celebrate National Park Week by visiting the parks and learning more about their significance.